summary:
HEROES CALLED MARVEL #13 - Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell) 
Marvel Comics very own Captain Marvel was created by writer-editor Stan...
body:
HEROES CALLED MARVEL #13 - Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell)

Marvel Comics very own Captain Marvel was created by writer-editor Stan Lee (and designed by Gene Colan). He first appeared in Marvel Super-Heroes #12 (December 1967). He was a human looking warrior by the name of Mar-Vell from the planet Kree sent to spy on Earth. He adopted the secret identity of a scientist named Walter Lawson, and wore his his green and white Kree military uniform to protect people. In one incident bystanders heard him incorrectly pronounce his name as “Captain Marvel”.


Captain Marvel was given his own series in May 1968.
